						               													<description>The game comes with a pack of cards illustrating, step-by-step, how to build the Rube Goldberg contraption.  That deck is dealt out randomly to the players.  The player with card 1 plays it, assembling the parts indicated on the card.  He continues playing cards in sequence if he can.  When he no longer can, he grabs a random card from the player to his left (unless it is that player's last card) --which may allow him to continue.  If not, the player who has the next card plays it, and so on.  The last card gives that player a chance to crank the clock and wake the sleeper (and win!).  If that fails, play passes to his right.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
